<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-203-002 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 440 163</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  March 11 1991 v25 n10 p73(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software group gets bitten by the quality bug. (software industryassociation Adapso to offer quality awards)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Margolis, Nell.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The software industry association Adapso has announced its firstannual quality award program.andP;  The program is inspired by the USDepartment of Commerce's Malcolm Baldridge National Quality Awardprogram and uses similar qualification procedures.andP;  Entrants gothrough a series of rigorous audits which benefit their qualitymanagement regardless of who actually wins the award.andP;  The Adapsoawards are more broadly defined than the Baldridge award and areaimed at spurring companies to improve their products andprocesses.andP;  Competition for the first annual Adapso awards islimited to members of the trade group's Software Industry andVertical Application and Remarketers divisions but will be open toall Adapso members in subsequent years.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Trade and professional associationsAchievements and AwardsQuality ControlAssociation of Data Processing Service OrganizationsSoftware Design.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>